fancy-weather.description:
The goal of the project was to create an app that allows users to check the weather almost in any place of the world, listen to audio forecast, control the app with the voice, change the background image, change the language of the app (en, ru, by).

FancyWeather was developed with the usage of side APIs. For example:
- Mapbox GJ JS for the map;
- Open Weather for weather forecasts;
- IP Info for getting user geolocation data;
- SpeechRecognition API for voice control;

Extra Libraries used in the app:
- react-i18next library was used for internationalization. There are 3 languages: English, Russian, Belarusian;
- Moment.JS for time formats;

Also, there are animated icons for the attractiveness of the application.
After the finishing of the app development, I sent it to my friends in order to check it for bugs. All my friends were happy with it. They said that the app looks attractive for the user and provides all the necessary features to check the weather. But there was one problem with used IP Info API. It sometimes showed the wrong places for small localities. But the feedback was positive.

todo.description:
The objective of the project was to create a ToDo app with the following functionality:

- Create and delete tasks;
- Sort tasks by deadlines;
- Change the view of the app (4 squares or a single list);
- Change the theme and the background image;

In order to develop this web-app, I used such modern libraries as React and Redux. Also, there was SCSS for styles.

At the end of the project, the main requirements were successfully completed.

